- 'Recent' refers to the most recent demographic entry and the latest user activity for each participant; 
- 'American' refers to participants with a nationality name 'USA'; 
- 'Right-handed' refers to participants with a handedness name 'Right'.

- 'matured into their nationality's seniority' refers to having an average age greater than 30 within their nationality; 
- 'a profession with a lucrative average income' refers to an average income by occupation greater than 50,000; 
- 'a sizeable group within their nationality and handedness category' refers to the count of participants greater than 5 when partitioned by nationality and handedness.
